 This plan implements standardized image artifact handling using `bioio` across all environments. Instead of custom wrappers, we leverage `bioio.BioImage` for consistent, lazy-loaded, 5D TCZYX access to microscopy data.
 
+## Constitution Gate
+- **P-I: Stable MCP Surface**: No change to public tool calling API; manifest schema expansion is backwards-compatible.
+- **P-II: Isolated Tool Execution**: `bioio` and plugins are installed in per-tool environments; core remains lightweight.
+- **P-III: Artifact References Only**: All I/O uses `ArtifactRef`; `bioio` provides the standardized reader for these references.
+- **P-IV: Reproducibility & Provenance**: Environments pinned via `conda-lock`; interchange formats declared in manifests.
+- **P-V: Safety & Observability**: File access remains restricted to allowlists; `bioio` used as a safe, industry-standard library.
+- **P-VI: Test-Driven Development**: All phases follow TDD, with contract/unit tests written before implementation.
+
